<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><entry xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xml:id="entry_færdyg" xml:lang="os"><form xml:lang="os-x-iron" type="lemma"><orth>færdyg</orth></form><form xml:lang="os-x-digor" type="dialectal"><orth>færdug</orth></form><sense><sense><cit type="translation" xml:lang="ru"><q>самоцвет</q></cit><cit type="translation" xml:lang="en"><q>gem</q></cit></sense><sense><cit type="translation" xml:lang="ru"><q>драгоценный камень</q></cit><cit type="translation" xml:lang="en"><q>jewel</q></cit></sense><sense><cit type="translation" xml:lang="ru"><q>бусинка</q></cit><cit type="translation" xml:lang="en"><q>bead</q></cit></sense></sense><re><form type="lemma"><orth>færdgutæ</orth></form><sense><sense><cit type="translation" xml:lang="ru"><q>бусы</q></cit><cit type="translation" xml:lang="en"><q>beads</q></cit></sense><sense><cit type="translation" xml:lang="ru"><q>ожерелье</q></cit><cit type="translation" xml:lang="en"><q>necklace</q></cit></sense></sense></re><cit type="exampleGroup" corresp="#sense_færdyg." n=""><cit type="example"><note type="comment" xml:lang=""/><note type="comment" xml:lang=""/><quote>cykūrajy færdyg</quote><cit type="translation" xml:lang="ru"><q>чудесный камень-самоцвет, доставляющий его обладателю счастье</q></cit><cit type="translation" xml:lang="en"><q>a wonderful gemstone that brings happiness to its owner</q></cit><note type="comment" xml:lang=""> ()</note><note type="comment" xml:lang=""> ()</note></cit></cit><cit type="exampleGroup" corresp="#sense_færdyg." n=""><cit type="example"><quote>ūrs dony bylyl saw færdyg</quote><cit type="translation" xml:lang="ru"><q>на берегу белой речки черный самоцвет</q></cit><cit type="translation" xml:lang="en"><q>black gem on the banks of the white river</q></cit><bibl><ref target="#src_Munk."/><biblScope>196</biblScope></bibl></cit></cit><cit type="exampleGroup" corresp="#sense_." n=""><cit type="example"><note type="comment" xml:lang=""/><note type="comment" xml:lang=""/><quote>cykūrajy færdyg</quote><cit type="translation" xml:lang="ru"><q>чудесный камень-самоцвет, доставляющий его обладателю счастье</q></cit><cit type="translation" xml:lang="en"><q>a wonderful gemstone that brings happiness to its owner</q></cit><note type="comment" xml:lang=""> ()</note><note type="comment" xml:lang=""> ()</note></cit></cit><cit type="exampleGroup" corresp="#sense_." n=""><cit type="example"><quote>ūrs dony bylyl saw færdyg</quote><cit type="translation" xml:lang="ru"><q>на берегу белой речки черный самоцвет</q></cit><cit type="translation" xml:lang="en"><q>black gem on the banks of the white river</q></cit><bibl><ref target="#src_Munk."/><biblScope>196</biblScope></bibl></cit></cit><etym xml:lang="ru">Вероятно, восходит к <mentioned xml:lang="ira"><lang/><w>*pardu-ka</w></mentioned>, где <mentioned xml:lang="ira"><lang/><w>*pardu-</w><note type="comment" xml:lang=""/><note type="comment" xml:lang=""/><gloss><q>пестрый</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="ira"><w/><gloss><q>яркий</q></gloss></mentioned>, ; ср. <mentioned xml:lang="sa"><lang/><w>pṛdāku-</w><gloss><q>змея</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="sa"><w/><gloss><q>тигр</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sa"><w/><gloss><q>пантера</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sa"><w/><note type="comment" xml:lang=""/><note type="comment" xml:lang=""/><gloss><q>пестрое (животное)</q></gloss></mentioned>, . Сюда же <mentioned xml:lang="fa"><lang/><w>pul</w><note type="comment" xml:lang=""> ()</note><note type="comment" xml:lang=""> ()</note><gloss><q>монета (‘блестящая’)</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="fa"><w/><gloss><q>рыбья чешуя</q></gloss></mentioned>,  и <mentioned xml:lang="kho"><lang/><w>palāā</w><note type="comment" xml:lang=""> ()</note><note type="comment" xml:lang=""> ()</note><gloss><q>цветы</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="kho"><w/><gloss><q>флаг</q></gloss></mentioned>,  (последнее слово связывают с пракритским %ipaṭākā%i, — <bibl><ref target="#ref_NTS"/><biblScope>XV 112</biblScope></bibl>). Древности названия отвечает древность предмета. Бусы как украшение обычны в сарматский период. „Рядовое население украшало свой костюм бусами и бисером. Обычай этот был широко распространен у сармат и появился на Кубани с проникновением сюда новых сарматских племен“ (<bibl><biblScope xml:lang="ru">Н. %sАнфимов%s. Древние поселения Прикубанья. Краснодар, 1953, стр. 66</biblScope><biblScope xml:lang="en">N. %sAnfimov%s. Ancient settlements of the Kuban region. Krasnodar, 1953, p. 66</biblScope></bibl>).</etym><etym xml:lang="en">Probably, traces back to <mentioned xml:lang="ira"><lang/><w>*pardu-ka</w></mentioned>, where <mentioned xml:lang="ira"><lang/><w>*pardu-</w><note type="comment" xml:lang=""/><note type="comment" xml:lang=""/><gloss><q>multicoloured</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="ira"><w/><gloss><q>bright</q></gloss></mentioned>, ; cf. <mentioned xml:lang="sa"><lang/><w>pṛdāku-</w><gloss><q>snake</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="sa"><w/><gloss><q>tiger</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sa"><w/><gloss><q>panther</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sa"><w/><note type="comment" xml:lang=""/><note type="comment" xml:lang=""/><gloss><q>multicoloured (animal)</q></gloss></mentioned>, . See also <mentioned xml:lang="fa"><lang/><w>pul</w><note type="comment" xml:lang=""> ()</note><note type="comment" xml:lang=""> ()</note><gloss><q>coin (‘shiny’)</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="fa"><w/><gloss><q>fish-scale</q></gloss></mentioned>,  and <mentioned xml:lang="kho"><lang/><w>palāā</w><note type="comment" xml:lang=""> ()</note><note type="comment" xml:lang=""> ()</note><gloss><q>flowers</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="kho"><w/><gloss><q>флаг</q></gloss></mentioned>,  (some people relate the latter word to Eteocretan %ipaṭākā%i, — <bibl><ref target="#ref_NTS"/><biblScope>XV 112</biblScope></bibl>). The antiquity of the name corresponds to the antiquity of the object. Beads as decoration are common in the Sarmatian period. “The ordinary population decorated their costume with beads. This custom was widespread among the Sarmatians and appeared in the Kuban with the penetration of new Sarmatian tribes here“ (<bibl><biblScope xml:lang="ru">Н. %sАнфимов%s. Древние поселения Прикубанья. Краснодар, 1953, стр. 66</biblScope><biblScope xml:lang="en">N. %sAnfimov%s. Ancient settlements of the Kuban region. Krasnodar, 1953, p. 66</biblScope></bibl>).</etym></entry>